annotationA: Something about silencing protein 10; Essential for gene silencing: has a role in the structure of silenced chromatin. May be involved in gene regulation during development. Binds RNA; Belongs to the SAS10 family
annotationB: Rat1 5'-3' exoribonuclease (Rat1) is a member of the 5'-3' exonuclease family. Rat1 is required for mRNA processing and mutations cause phenotypes in various cell types, including the nervous system
